    Class and Description
    BoardModel
    The 'Model' side of the Director aspect of the Animation Suite.
    ColorHolder
    Generates and holds an ArrayList of MyColor.
    Model
    An abstract class for implementation by BoardModel and ViewModel to inherit from.
    MyColor
    This class is simply a custom Color class that takes a character in it's constructor for use with the text based 2D char Array.
    NewProjectMenu
    Sets up a JPanel to be called by the 'New Project' MenuItem in SuiteDirector.
    PreferencesMenu
    Sets up a JPanel for the 'Preferences' menu called when a users clicks the Preferences MenuItem in SuiteDirector.
    PreviewMaker
    Creates small 'preview' images of each frame in the animation
    RecentItemsMenu
    Represents a menu that holds a list of recently used items.
    SuiteCanvas
    The Swing for the Director side of the application, handling how the user draws on the grid in BoardModel.
    SuiteViewer
    This class is the Player version of the Director's 'SuiteCanvas'.
    Tabs
    Tabs is the overall application Frame, that holds the JPanels for the Director and Display in tabs.
    ViewModel
    The Model for the Player side of the Animation Suite
